# 3D interactive (project-local)

When the open workspace contains **`.cursor/skills/r3f-three/`**:

1. Read **`.cursor/skills/r3f-three/SKILL.md`** before WebGL / R3F work — proof scene gate first.
2. Follow **`.cursor/rules/3d-interactive-lane.mdc`** when present.
3. Stack lookup: `python .cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "<topic>" --stack react-three-fiber`
4. Inspiration: **`.cursor/design-refs/3d.md`**

## Hybrid repos (UI + WebGL)

If **Impeccable** is also installed:

- **WebGL / scenes only** → this lane. Skip Impeccable CSS detectors on canvas code.
- **Dashboard / forms / Tailwind** → `frontend-design-lane.mdc` + Impeccable.
- Routing: [HYBRID.md](https://github.com/darkyzowo/cursor-agent-stack/blob/master/docs/HYBRID.md).

If r3f-three is not installed, this rule is inert. Install: [docs/3D.md](https://github.com/darkyzowo/cursor-agent-stack/blob/master/docs/3D.md).

Do not duplicate checkpoint hooks in project `.cursor/hooks.json` — session memory hooks live in global `~/.cursor/hooks.json`.
